    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>N York</placeName>, <date>Nov 2.
                5621/1860</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir—</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><sic>Inclosed</sic> the continuation<lb/> of the “Declaration of
                Independence.” I<lb/> thought the portion sent to you at first,<lb/> was enough for
                    <hi rend="underline">two</hi> weeks, as I<lb/> wish to spin out the publication till<lb/>
                <date>Chanukah</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your correspondent “<hi rend="underline"
                        ><persName>Counsellor</persName></hi>” deals<lb/> in contemptible duplicity.
                He says: “<persName>Rev.<lb/> Dr Fishel</persName> &amp;c &amp;c.” (page 189, col.
                3) What<lb/> is the truth? 104 votes were cast, of<lb/> these
                    <persName>F.</persName> received 53, that is to say, he<lb/> was reelected by a
                majority of two<lb/> votes. If he had yet one spark of<lb/> pride and principle left
                in him, he<lb/> would have respectfully declined; but<lb/> no, even because half of
                the congregati<lb/>on do not want him, he will take<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">their</hi> money and they <hi rend="underline">must</hi> listen
                to<lb/> him, or he will receive <del>their</del> insult<lb/> offered to him by their
                leaving the Syna-</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>gogue when he ascends the pulpit. Be-<lb/>sides, he has been reelected only for
                one<lb/> year. Oh! He is a man of principle<lb/> &amp; character. Counsel your correspondent<lb/>
                <persName><sic>counsellor</sic></persName> to be more candid &amp; truth-<lb/>ful in
                future.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Why have you not a word of<lb/> censure for the attempted vandalism
                of <persName>Dr<lb/> Sachs</persName> of <placeName>Berlin</placeName>? To me, that
                man is<lb/> henceforth more hateful &amp; obnoxious than<lb/> even
                    <persName>Cardinal Antonelli</persName>. Why have<lb/> you not yet said a word
                about the<lb/> fanatic acts of the Orthodox of
                    <placeName>Amster-<lb/>dam</placeName>. Yet, you scold, because “rich
                Re-<lb/>formers” will not suffer themselves to be<lb/> brow-beaten into hypocrisy by
                ortho-<lb/>dox fanatics &amp; hypocrites. I am open<lb/> with you: I sometimes get
                perplexed<lb/> in my respect for the <hi rend="underline">Orthodox</hi>;<lb/> for
                withholding truth borders very<lb/> closely upon uttering untruth!”</p>
            <p>I was not present at the Banquet;<lb/> but I <hi rend="underline">know</hi> that the
                “rich reformers” re-</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>mained uncovered during “<hi rend="underline">Benschen</hi>”,<lb/> which awful
                sacrilegious act did not<lb/> present the Hospital from making<lb/> $14.000 by the
                operation.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">By the bye; The Keneseth Israel<lb/> of
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                <del>of</del>
                <hi rend="underline">begged</hi> me again<lb/> after <add>?</add> to become their
                minister, but<lb/> I declined again. No doubt, this my<lb/> seeming hardheartedness
                induced<lb/> them to accompany the two silver goblets<lb/> which they sent me with
                rather stiff &amp;<lb/> cold resolutions, and to do the thing<lb/> so very
                privately!! “<hi rend="underline"><add>?</add></hi>!”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">There is general dissatisfaction among<lb/> the Portuguese; this
                Synagogue is a<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">complete failure</hi>; they think already<lb/> of abandoning
                it. The “rich reformers”<lb/> will build a “<hi rend="underline">Temple</hi>” that
                will throw<lb/> all Synagogues here into darkness.<lb/> Concerning the
                    <placeName>Norfolk Street</placeName> Synagogue,<lb/> I can say: Put it down as
                a <hi rend="underline">Re</hi>-<lb/><hi rend="underline">form</hi> concern;
                    <persName>Dr Gruenebaum</persName> will<lb/> manage it; he comes out in his
                true</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>having been elected as Reformer;<lb/> and let me tell you into a secret:<lb/> a
                third, <hi rend="underline">American</hi>-Reform-Congregati-<lb/>on will soon spring
                into existence!!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">God speed it <add>כן יוסיף וכן אצליח</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours, as ever,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">M Mayer</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Please send me one or<lb/> two more copies of the<lb/> paper
                containing the<lb/> “Declaration of Indep.”<lb/> as I wish to send one<lb/> to
                    <persName>Stein</persName>.</p>
        </body>
